Day 3 in Who Am I Anyway? ~ I am Significant ⠀
⠀
Ephesians 3:12 "In him and through faith we may approach God with freedom and confidence."⠀
⠀
⠀
One of the things I strive for as a parent is for my children to feel they can come to me with anything.  I want to be approachable to them simply because of my love for them and my desire to give them every chance I humanly can at success in life.  Basically, my children are significant to me. ⠀
⠀
⠀
Just as my children are significant to me, I, as a child of the King of kings and Lord of lords am significant to Him.  He created me, He desires to be intimately involved in the details of my life and He loved me so much He died for me so He can spend eternity with me.  He did that for you too.  Do you believe that?⠀
⠀
⠀
Let's pray today for the Holy Spirit to fill each of us with a true sense of our significance to God.  As He fills us with that reality, let's share with our children their significance to Him.⠀
⠀
⠀
Dear Heavenly Father, thank you for the privilege of approaching you with freedom and confidence, not because of who I am but because of who you are.  Thank you for your desire to be intimately involved in the smallest details of my life.  Fill me today with a sense of my significance to you, and, in turn may I teach my children that they are fearfully and wonderfully made by you and they matter to you.  May they find freedom to approach you with confidence.  In Jesus' Name, Amen!⠀
⠀
